Pxlkit Licensing Overview
=========================

Pxlkit uses a split licensing model so that software code, icon/art assets, and trademarks are governed separately.

1. Code license — see `LICENSE-CODE`
   Applies to the source code for `@pxlkit/core`, `@pxlkit/ui-kit`, `@pxlkit/voxel`, the Next.js app source, repo scripts, and documentation text unless a file is clearly identified as an asset or third-party material.

2. Asset license — see `LICENSE-ASSETS`
   Applies to the icon-pack packages (`@pxlkit/gamification`, `@pxlkit/feedback`, `@pxlkit/social`, `@pxlkit/weather`, `@pxlkit/ui`, `@pxlkit/effects`, `@pxlkit/parallax`), exported icon data, artwork, illustrations, screenshots, marketing images, and other visual assets unless another notice says otherwise.

3. Commercial terms — see `COMMERCIAL_TERMS`
   Paid plans remove the attribution requirement for assets licensed under `LICENSE-ASSETS`. They do not change the MIT license for code packages.

4. Trademark policy — see `TRADEMARK_POLICY`
   The Pxlkit name, logo, and brand presentation are not licensed by the code or asset licenses.

5. Third-party notices — see `THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES`
   Third-party software, SDKs, fonts, and assets remain subject to their own licenses.

6. Contributor terms — see `CONTRIBUTOR_LICENSE.md`
   Contributions are accepted under terms that keep code MIT-compatible while allowing asset contributions to remain usable under the repository's asset and commercial model.

If there is any conflict between these documents, the more specific document for the relevant file or asset controls.

Licensing questions: info@pxlkit.xyz
